    "title": "Meiosis (I Dream Of Sex)",
    "description": "If both new ideas and new chromosomes are generated by recombination, is Meiosis a state of matter or a state of mind? \n\nThoughts tend to melt, thaw, and resolve themselves into a Do.  \n\n~~~~~~~~~~\n\n&quot;Chemistry without catalysis, would be a sword without a handle, a light without brilliance, a bell without sound.&quot;\n— Alwin Mittasch\n\n&quot;Before we talk about ecosystem design, we have to talk about ego-system management.&quot;\n— William McDonough\n\n&quot;Cogitatio in vero exquirendo maxime versatur. Appetitus impellit ad agendum.&quot;\n[The Intellect engages us in the pursuit of Truth. The Passions impel us to Action.] \n— Marcus Tullius Cicero\n\n&quot;After death, life reappears in a different form and with different laws. It is inscribed in the laws of the permanence of life on the surface of the earth and everything that has been a plant and an animal will be destroyed and transformed into a gaseous, volatile and mineral substance.&quot; \n— Louis Pasteur",
